Package net.ashwork.functionality.throwable.abstracts Description

The interfaces in this package are annotated with InheritOnly. These are meant as the interface should only be inherited and never used directly as a functional interface. You can obtain an abstract version of an interface from a declarable one, but it should not be constructed directly as otherwise an error will most likely occur.

This specific package (excluding subclasses) only holds the basic abstract throwing Functions.
